<section xml:id="sec-double-angle-identities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Double-Angle Identities</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Identities about double angles can be derived from the sum and difference identities.
    </p>
    
    <md>
      <mrow>
        \begin{array}{ccc}
        \boxed{\sin{2\theta} = 2\sin{\theta}\cos{\theta}} \amp \quad \boxed{\begin{array}{rl}
        \cos{2\theta} \amp = \cos^2{\theta} - \sin^2{\theta} \\
        \amp = 2\cos^2{\theta} - 1 \\
        \amp = 1 - 2\sin^2{\theta}
        \end{array}}
        \amp \quad \boxed{\tan{2\theta} = \frac{2\tan{\theta}}{1 - \tan^2{\theta}}}
        \end{array}
      </mrow>
    </md>
    
    <p>
      These are expressions for the trigonometric ratios of double angles (<m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m>, and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>), in terms of their associated <q>single</q> angles (<m>\sin{\theta}, \cos{\theta}</m>, and <m>\tan{\theta}</m>).
    </p>
  </introduction>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-finding-exact-value-examples">
    <title>Finding Exact Value Examples</title>
    
    <project xml:id="project-evaluate-exact-expressions">
      <title>Evaluate Expressions Exactly</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Evaluate each expression exactly, using a double-angle identity.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>2 \sin{\frac{\pi}{12}} \cos{\frac{\pi}{12}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{1}{2}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\cos^2{\brac{\frac{\pi}{3}}} - \sin^2{\brac{\frac{\pi}{3}}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>-\frac{1}{2}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{2 \tan \frac{\pi}{6}}{1 - \tan^2 \frac{\pi}{6}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sqrt{3}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>1 - 2 \sin^2 15^\circ</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\cos^2 \frac{\pi}{3} - \sin^2 \frac{\pi}{3}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>-\frac{1}{2}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>2 \sin \frac{\pi}{6} \cos \frac{\pi}{6}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="project-expand-expressions">
      <title>Expand Expressions</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Expand each expression, using a double-angle identity.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>3\sin{4x}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p><m>4x = 2 \cdot 2x</m> (<m>2x</m> is double <m>2x</m>)</p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>6\sin{2x}\cos{2x}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>4\tan{6x}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p><m>6x = 2 \cdot 3x</m> (<m>6x</m> is double <m>3x</m>)</p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{8\tan{3x}}{1 - \tan^2{3x}}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{1}{2}\sin{\frac{1}{2}x}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p><m>\frac{1}{2}x = 2 \cdot \frac{1}{4}x</m></p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{\frac{x}{4}}\cos{\frac{x}{4}}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{1}{4}\tan{\frac{1}{2}x}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{1}{2}\cdot\frac{\tan{\frac{x}{4}}}{1 - \tan^2{\frac{x}{4}}}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-exact-values-variable-angles">
    <title>Exact Values with Variable Angles</title>
    
    <project xml:id="project-exact-values-variables">
      <title>Find Exact Values from Information</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Find the exact value of each trigonometric ratio, from the given information.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><p>If <m>\sin{\theta} = \frac{12}{13}</m>, where <m>\frac{\pi}{2} \lt \theta \lt \pi</m>, then find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{169}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{119}{169}, \tan{(2\theta)} = \frac{120}{119}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p>Let <m>\cos{\theta} = -\frac{7}{25}</m> and <m>\ang{90} \lt \theta \lt \ang{180}</m>. Find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = -\frac{336}{625}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{527}{625}, \tan{(2\theta)} = \frac{336}{527}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p>Let <m>\theta</m> be an angle in quadrant III with <m>\cos{\theta} = -\frac{8}{17}</m>. find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = \frac{240}{289}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{161}{289}, \tan{(2\theta)} = -\frac{240}{161}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p>If <m>\sin{\theta} = -\frac{12}{13}</m> and <m>\theta</m> is in quadrant III, find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = \frac{120}{169}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{119}{169}, \tan{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{119}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p>If <m>\sin{\theta} = \frac{5}{13}</m> and <m>\frac{\pi}{2} \lt \theta \lt \pi</m>. Find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{169}, \cos{(2\theta)} = \frac{119}{169}, \tan{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{119}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p>If <m>\cos{\theta} = -\frac{3}{5}</m> and <m>\theta</m> is in quadrant III, find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}</m>.</p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{24}{25}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-simplify-using-identities">
    <title>Simplify Using Double-Angle Identities</title>
    
    <project xml:id="project-simplify-expressions">
      <title>Simplify Expressions</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each expression as a single trigonometric function.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>2 \sin{(4x)} \cos{(4x)}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{(8x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>10 \cos^2{x} - 5</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>5 \cos{(2x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>2 \sin{\brac{\frac{1}{2} x}} \cos{\brac{\frac{1}{2} x}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\sin{x}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>1 - 2 \sin^2{(3x)}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\cos{(6x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{4\tan{(3x)}}{1 - \tan^2{(3x)}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>2 \tan{(6x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{\cos{(2x)} + 1}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p>choose the double angle for cosine which cancels out the 1 in the denominator</p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>\tan{x}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\cos^3{x}}{\cos(2x) + \sin^2{x}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\cos{x}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\cos{(2x)} + 1}{2 \cos{x}}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p>choose the double angle for cosine which cancels out the <m>1</m> in the numerator</p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>\cos{x}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\sin 2x}{2 \sin x}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\cos x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\cos 2x - 1}{2 \sin x}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p>choose the double angle for cosine which cancels out the <m>-1</m> in the numerator</p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>-\sin x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\sin^3 x}{\cos 2x - \cos^2 x}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{\sin x}{2}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>6 \sin{(8x)} \cos{(8x)}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>3 \sin{(16x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>4 \sin^2{(2x)} - 2</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>-2 \cos{(4x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{3-6\sin^2{x}}{2\sin{x}\cos{x}}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>3 \cot{(2x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\brac{\sin^2{x} - \cos^2{x}}^2 - \sin^2{(2x)}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p>use a double-angle identity, do not expand</p></hint>
        <answer><p><m>\cos{(4x)}</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>4\sin 3x\cos 3x</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>2\sin 6x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>6\sin^2 x-3</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>-3\cos 2x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>4\cos^2 5x-4\sin^2 5x</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>4\cos 10x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>4\cos^2 2x-2</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>2\cos 4x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{6\tan 4x}{1-\tan^2 4x}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>3\tan 8x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{2\tan 2x}{3-3\tan^2 2x}</m></p></statement>
        <answer><p><m>\frac{1}{3}\tan 4x</m></p></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
