        <statement><p><m>\frac{2\tan{x}}{1+\tan^2{x}} = \sin{(2x)}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p>convert to sine and cosine, clear denominators, Pythagorean identity, double-angle identity</p></hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\frac{\sin{(6x)}}{1 + \cos{(6x)}} = \tan{(3x)}</m></p></statement>
        <hint><p>work with both sides, double-angle identity, cancel common factors</p></hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><p><m>\tan{(2x)} = \frac{2}{\cot{x} - \tan{x}}</m></p></statement>
