    <exercise>
      <title>Exact Value with Variables</title>
      <statement><p>Given that <m>\cos\theta=\frac{a}{x}</m> and <m>\theta</m> is in quadrant <m>4</m>, find the exact value of <m>\sin 2\theta</m> in terms of <m>x</m>.</p></statement>
      <hint><p><m>\sin 2\theta=2\sin\theta\cos\theta</m></p></hint>
      <answer><p><m>\sin 2\theta=-\frac{2a\sqrt{x^2-a^2}}{x^2}</m></p></answer>
